Max M. TANNENBAUM v. P. BALLAN-TINE & SONS, Appellant. No. 9356. Circuit Court of Appeals, Third Circuit Argued June 2, 1947. Decided June 16, 1947. Andrew B. Crummy, of Newark, N.J. (William A. Consodine, of Newark, N. J., on the brief), for appellant. Joseph B. Schwartz, Asst. U. S. Atty., of Newark, N. J. (Edgar H. Rossbach, U. S. Atty., of Newark, N.J., on the brief), for appellee.

Before BIGGS, MARIS, and O’CON-NELL, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment of the court below is affirmed.
